osophic life and the case for that life as the most natural, the freest, or, in short, the best or most choice-worthy of lives. Cooper focuses especially on a single feature, arguably the defining feature of the philosophic life: the overcoming of the ordinary moral consciousness in favor of the cognitivist view of morality. Cooper shows that Rousseau, with his particular understanding and embrace of the philosophic life, proves to be a kind of latter-day Socratic. Thorough and thought-provoking, Dreaming of Justice, Waking to Wisdom provides vital insight into Rousseau.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aPhilosophy in literature. 0aPhilosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh  aJean-Jacques Rousseau, philosophic life, Socratic, Reveries, Plato's Republic, moral consciousness, seeing what is, nature, personal dependence, philosopher-king.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2023 Englishz978311131922308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2023z9783111318646oZDB-23-DPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2023z97831107973290 cprintz978022682499440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226825007423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226825007/original  a978-3-11-079732-9  University of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131922-3  EBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2023  aZDB-23-DPHb2023